flowchart LR
  subgraph intent["Recovered Segment 6A design"]
    A0["S0 Gate and seal<br/>Verifies Layer-1 and Layer-2 PASS authority<br/>and freezes the Layer-3 input world"]
    A1["S1 Party-base authority<br/>Realises the customer and party universe"]
    A2["S2 Account and product authority<br/>Turns parties into accounts and holdings"]
    A3["S3 Instrument authority<br/>Turns accounts into credentials and payment handles"]
    A4["S4 Device/IP graph authority<br/>Turns entities into a static access graph"]
    A5["S5 Static fraud posture and final gate<br/>Assigns roles and seals segment legitimacy"]
  end

  A0 --> A1 --> A2 --> A3 --> A4 --> A5

  B0["Actual design shifts that matter"] --> B1["S0 became a real Layer-3 multi-law gate:<br/>it had to verify all upstream bundle forms while keeping sealing lightweight for large row-level inputs"]
  B0 --> B2["S1 remained the party-universe authority,<br/>but adopted lean execution choices such as aggregated RNG evidence and deterministic region mapping"]
  B0 --> B3["S2 became the first major remediation owner surface:<br/>hard post-merge K_max enforcement changed what account realism actually means"]
  B0 --> B4["S3 stayed narrower than S2 and S4:<br/>it extends the product world into credential reality without becoming the main realism repair lane"]
  B0 --> B5["S4 became the main network-realism owner surface:<br/>IP prior alignment, linkage coverage, and bounded reuse tails are what made the graph credible"]
  B0 --> B6["S5 became both static fraud-posture authority and the final risk-propagation gate,<br/>not just a receipt writer"]

